3. ST-T1024: A Security-By-Design Architecture

3.1 The Six-Step Deterministic Pipeline

Step Component Security Implication
1 Intent Harvesting Normalized input → no malicious injection
2 FIS Triage Deterministic routing → no misdirection
3 FSM Scheduling Hardware-enforced timing → no DoS
4 Tile Activation Only one tile powered → isolation
5 Execution Ternary logic → no floating-point surprises
6 0V Power-Down Immediate idle → zero attack surface

3.2 Security Properties Inherent to ST-T1024

Property Mechanism IEC 62443 Alignment
Immutability 75% ROM — hardware-burned, unchangeable FR 3 (System Integrity)
Isolation Domain tiling — each tile independent Zone and Conduit model
Air-Gapping No network interface — local execution only FR 5 (Restricted Data Flow)
Determinism No stochastic behavior — all states known FR 3, FR 6 (Auditability)
AET Assured Execution Time — 680 ns, constant FR 7 (Resource Availability)
Sovereign Updates SK-1024 — encrypted, signed, authorized FR 1, FR 2 (Authentication)
Fail-Safe 0x-AMBIG on ambiguous queries FR 6 (Timely Response)

